Evaluate Benchmark of HCC1395

QBiC

1 Introduction

For somatic benchmarking a dataset from the HCC1395 cell line was run through the pipeline by combining each mapper with all variant callers.

2 Loading the dataset

Truth vcf & bed files were downloaded from here, following the links from this paper.

See script.sh for details on how som.py was run.

3 Methods

plot_scatter <- function (data, title) {
    ggplot(data, aes(precision,recall, color= caller, fill = caller, shape = mapper)) +
    geom_jitter(width= 0.02, height = 0.02) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits=seq(0,1))+
  # ggscatter(data , x = "precision", y = "recall", 
  #           color = "caller", fill = "caller", 
  #           shape ="mapper", size = 2, 
  #           title = title, ylim= c(0,1), xlim = c(0,1), 
  #           palette = "npg", position = position_jitter()) + 
    guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=2, alpha = 1))) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust=1, size=10),
         axis.text.y = element_text(size=10),
         axis.title.x = element_blank(),
         legend.position="top",  legend.box="vertical", legend.margin=margin())
}
